How to Install the 'etrobo environment'


Windows:
1. Install 'Windows Services for Linux'(WSL1)
2. Install 'Ubuntu 18.04 LTS' for WSL from the Microsoft Store
3. Install 'Microsoft Visual Studio Code'
4. Open 'Windows Command Prompt' and run this command:

cd /d "%USERPROFILE%\Desktop" & echo wsl if [ ! -f ~/startetrobo ]; then wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ETrobocon/etrobo/master/scripts/startetrobo -O ~/startetrobo; chmod +x ~/startetrobo; fi; ~/startetrobo > "Start ETrobo.cmd"

5. Double-click 'Start ETrobo.cmd' on your desktop, or run `./startetrobo` on Ubuntu terminal
6. Follow instalation message
7. After a VSCode is starting up automatically, open a integrated terminal of VSCode and run `make sample`

Mac:
1. Install 'Microsoft Visual Studio Code'
2. Run VSCode
3. Open 'Command Pallet', type `install code` and install 'PATH' by click this context
4. Close VSCode
5. Open 'Terminal' and run this command:

cd Desktop; echo 'name=startetrobo_mac.command; if [ ! -f $name ]; then curl -O https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ETrobocon/etrobo/master/scripts/$name; chmod +x ~/$name; fi; ~/$name' > "Start ETrobo.command"; chmod +x "Start ETrobo.command"

5. Double-click 'Start ETrobo.command' on your desktop, or run `./startetrobo_mac.command` on Ubuntu terminal
6. Follow instalation message
7. After a VSCode is starting up automatically, open a integrated terminal of VSCode and run `make sample`


ChromeOS:
1. Install 'Linux(Beta)'
2. Download a Debian package of 'Microsoft Visual Studio Code' from its download site
3. Double-click it to install onto 'Linux(beta)'
2. Open 'Terminal' in 'Linux app'
3. Follow below section 3. of Linux installation


Linux:
1. Install 'Microsoft Visual Studio Code'
2. Open 'Terminal'
3. Run this command:

wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ETrobocon/etrobo/master/scripts/startetrobo -O ~/startetrobo; chmod +x ~/startetrobo; ~/startetrobo

4. Run `./startetrobo`
5. Follow instalation message
6. After a VSCode is starting up automatically, open a integrated terminal of VSCode and run `make sample`

